# Portfolio workspace — Notion database specification

Use this as the blueprint for the CEO's Portfolio Notion workspace. Built during Phase 11 of `/deploy-project`, referenced every time a new project is registered into the portfolio.

## Workspace

**Name convention:** `[CEO-handle] — Portfolio`
- Example: `Jakub — Portfolio`
- Creates clear separation from any company workspace
- Use your most-trusted Notion login (NOT a shared alias)

**Access list:**
- CEO (owner)
- Up to 2 trusted delegates (typical: COO, chief of staff, family office principal) — document each delegate's role + date added

**Workspace icon / cover:** optional but helpful — use something distinctly NOT tied to any single company brand, to reinforce this is a meta-layer.

## Three required databases

### Database 1: Projects

One row per company you manage. The master index of the portfolio.

| Property | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| **Name** | Title | Project handle (e.g. "ACME", "Clinic-X", "AlphaStudio") |
| **Full company name** | Rich text | Legal entity name |
| **Industry** | Select | Food & bev / Medical / Interior / Finance / Tech / Manufacturing / Family office / Professional services / Other |
| **Stage** | Select | Pre-launch / Launch / Scale-up / Mature / Turnaround / Wind-down / Paused |
| **Status** | Select | Green / Yellow / Red (CEO's gut-check on current health) |
| **My role** | Select | Founder / CEO / Chairman / Director / Advisor / LP / Other |
| **Ownership %** | Number | Your economic share if applicable |
| **Notion workspace URL** | URL | Link to the company's Notion workspace |
| **MEMORY.md path** | Rich text | Local path to the project's memory file |
| **Project root folder** | Rich text | Local path to the project root |
| **Current P0 count** | Number | Auto-updated by weekly digest |
| **Current P1 count** | Number | Auto-updated by weekly digest |
| **Team size** | Number | FTE (roughly) — internal only |
| **Revenue band** | Select | Pre-revenue / <€100k / €100k-1M / €1M-5M / €5M-25M / €25M+ — internal only |
| **Cash runway** | Select | <3 months / 3-6 months / 6-12 months / 12-24 months / 24+ months / N/A — internal only |
| **Latest material event** | Rich text | Most recent big thing (launch, win, loss, pivot) — auto-updated |
| **Next review** | Date | When CEO plans to sit down with this project deeply |
| **Last digest** | Date | Auto-updated by weekly digest |
| **Deployed date** | Date | When this project was onboarded via /deploy-project |
| **Integration map note** | Rich text | Which integrations are authenticated for this project; Claude updates |
| **Critical dependencies** | Rich text | Single-supplier risks, key-person risks, regulatory risks |
| **Notes** | Rich text | CEO freetext |

**Views:**

- **All Projects (Table)** — default landing
- **By Stage (Kanban)** — group by Stage
- **By Industry (Kanban)** — group by Industry
- **Needs attention (Filter)** — Status = Yellow OR Red, sort by Last digest
- **Active only (Filter)** — Status != Paused AND Stage != Wind-down
- **Review calendar (Timeline)** — sorted by Next review
- **Map (Map view if available)** — for geo-distributed portfolio

### Database 2: Weekly Digests

One entry per project per week. Auto-populated every Monday morning by a scheduled task that queries each registered project's MEMORY.md + Notion Tasks DB + recent deliverables.

| Property | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| **Name** | Title | `[YYYY-Www] [Project] digest` — e.g. "2026-W16 ACME digest" |
| **Week starting** | Date | Monday of the week |
| **Project** | Relation | Link to Projects DB row |
| **One-line status** | Rich text | The headline — what happened this week |
| **Key metric delta** | Rich text | Revenue / traffic / conversion / whatever matters most, this-week vs last-week |
| **P0 opened** | Number | New P0s this week |
| **P0 closed** | Number | P0s closed this week |
| **P0 currently open** | Number | Snapshot at digest time |
| **Material events** | Rich text | Meaningful changes (launches, losses, wins, regulatory, personnel) |
| **Decisions needed from CEO** | Rich text | Anything flagged for CEO attention this week |
| **Blocked items** | Rich text | What's stuck and why |
| **Team / resourcing flag** | Rich text | Staffing issues, vendor issues, budget concerns |
| **Wins worth noting** | Rich text | Positive developments |
| **Deliverable highlights** | Rich text | Files produced this week worth noting |

**Views:**

- **This Week (Filter: Week starting = this week)** — the Monday-morning scan view
- **By Project (Kanban grouped by Project)** — trajectory per company
- **Timeline (Calendar by Week starting)** — pattern view over time
- **Recent Wins (Filter: Wins populated)** — optimism surface
- **Needs Decision (Filter: Decisions-needed populated)** — feeds `/review` input

### Database 3: Escalations

Cross-project issues needing CEO attention. Created manually or by Claude when ticket-level escalation criteria trigger.

| Property | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| **Name** | Title | Concise issue headline |
| **Date raised** | Date | When flagged |
| **Project** | Relation | Link to Projects DB (may be multi-select if cross-project) |
| **Type** | Select | Financial / Legal / Regulatory / Personnel / Vendor / Customer / Reputational / Operational / Strategic / Other |
| **Severity** | Select | Critical / High / Medium / Low |
| **Source** | Select | Weekly digest / Ad-hoc / Auto-triggered / Team escalation |
| **CEO action needed** | Rich text | What the CEO must do |
| **Context** | Rich text | Background |
| **Deadline** | Date | When does this need to be handled by |
| **Status** | Select | Open / In progress / Resolved / Deferred / Escalated further |
| **Resolution notes** | Rich text | Filled when closed |
| **Related tickets** | Rich text | IDs in project's Tasks DB |

**Views:**

- **Open (Filter: Status = Open / In progress)** — default
- **By Severity (Board grouped by Severity)** — triage view
- **By Project** — which company has most escalations (pattern spotting)
- **Resolved this quarter** — learnings

### Optional Database 4: Integration Map

One entry per Claude / Notion / tool integration across the portfolio. Helps audit at the quarterly privacy check.

| Property | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| **Name** | Title | `[Integration] on [Workspace]` — e.g. "Notion MCP on ACME workspace" |
| **Integration** | Select | Notion / Shopify / GA4 / Stripe / [etc.] |
| **Workspace / Account** | Rich text | Which workspace/account this integration is authenticated on |
| **Project** | Relation | Link to Projects DB |
| **Scope granted** | Rich text | Which pages/DBs/resources accessible |
| **Authenticated on (date)** | Date | Install date |
| **Last audit** | Date | Last privacy check |
| **Next audit** | Date | Next quarterly check |
| **Status** | Select | Active / Paused / Deprecated |
| **Secrets storage** | Select | System keychain / env var / 1Password / other |

**Views:**

- **Active (Filter: Status = Active)** — default
- **By Project** — integrations per company
- **Audit due (Filter: Next audit < today + 14 days)** — quarterly anchor

## Setup sequence (one-time per CEO)

1. Create the workspace
2. Create the four databases in order (Projects → Weekly Digests → Escalations → Integration Map)
3. Configure all views
4. Add Claude integration to the workspace + scope to the four DBs only
5. Add first delegates if applicable
6. Run smoke test: create one dummy project, one dummy digest, one dummy escalation; verify relationships work; delete dummies
7. Document the workspace at `~/[CEO-handle]-portfolio/README.md` (if using file backup) — URL, member list, integration ID, setup date

## Recurring cadence (scheduled tasks)

- **Weekly digest run** — every Monday 07:00 local time, Claude queries each Projects-DB row, writes one Weekly Digests entry per project, updates Projects DB fields (P0 count, Last digest, Latest material event)
- **Quarterly privacy audit** — first working day of Jan/Apr/Jul/Oct, Claude (or CEO manually) runs the privacy audit checklist from `references/portfolio-architecture.md`, logs results at `operations/privacy-audit-log.md`
- **Annual portfolio review** — first working day of January, Claude generates an annual summary across all projects, ready for year-opening strategy session

## Integration with `/deploy-project`

When a new project is onboarded:

1. Phase 11 checks: does a portfolio exist?
2. If yes → registers the new project into the Projects DB (creates the row)
3. If no → asks CEO whether to create the portfolio now (Phase 11 portfolio-setup)

When an existing project wasn't onboarded via `/deploy-project` originally but should be in the portfolio now:

1. Run `/deploy-project register-into-portfolio`
2. Specify the project's local path, Notion workspace URL, memory path
3. Skill populates the Projects DB row with best-guess values
4. CEO reviews + confirms

## Template content for the first Projects DB rows

When setting up, pre-populate with your existing companies to avoid empty-DB paralysis. For each:

- Name it
- Fill Industry + Stage + Status (Green/Yellow/Red)
- Fill My role + Ownership %
- Leave metric fields empty — they auto-fill after first `/deploy-project register-into-portfolio` run

## Digest format example

Every Monday, Claude posts something like this into Weekly Digests for each project:

```
Name: 2026-W17 ACME digest
Week starting: 2026-04-20
Project: ACME
One-line status: Packeta Shopify app deployed Monday; EU delivery now live across 7 markets. Legal policies published earlier. First agentic-ready state.
Key metric delta: DTC traffic +12% WoW (seasonal), email open rate steady 38%
P0 opened: 1 · P0 closed: 2 · P0 currently open: 3
Material events: Packeta paid subscription active; ODR link removed site-wide (TECH-024 done)
Decisions needed from CEO: Approve ACME-TECH-025 cookie consent engineering spend (~€1,500, External owner)
Blocked items: ACME-OPS-042 (Palugyay acquisition date) waiting on board-archive check
Team / resourcing flag: none
Wins worth noting: First EU cross-border order within 24h of Packeta live
Deliverable highlights: output/reports/260420 - ACME Packeta Deploy Summary.html
```

CEO scans all project digests in one view Monday morning. Total read time per week: 5-10 min across the whole portfolio.
